ifer Falls]]''\n|Cheryl\n|\"Triangle\"\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Jane the Virgin]]''\n|Wendy\n|\"Chapter Sixteen\"\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Battle Creek (TV series)|Battle Creek]]''\n|Susan\n|\"Stockholm\"\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Wisdom of the Crowd]]''\n|Karen Sanford\n|\"Trojan Horse\"\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Kevin (Probably) Saves the World]]''\n|Phoebe Powell\n|\"Caught White-Handed\"\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[The Resident (TV series)|The Resident]]''\n|Claudia Webb\n|\"Run, Doctor, Run\"\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Summer Camp Island]]''\n|Sue Peltzer (voice)\n|Main cast\n|-\n|2019\n|[[The OA]]\n|Amy Broderick\n|\"Mirror Mirror\"\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Album\n! Songs\n! Performers\n|-\n|1998\n|''Pitch Like a Girl''\n|\n# \"Whatever It Takes\" (4:24)\n# \"No One Can Touch Me\" (4:47)\n# \"Wish We Never Met\" (4:36)\n# \"Olivia Says\" (3:56)\n# \"Symphony\" (5:00)\n# \"Suck the Joy\" (3:45)\n# \"Look But Don't Touch\" (4:31)\n# \"Dumb Ol' Girl\" (3:39)\n# \"Old Familiar\" (4:13)\n# \"Yard Sale\" (5:28)\n# \"Stop Yelling\" (3:49)\n# \"Pick Up Where You Left Off\" (4:01)\n| Kathleen Wilhoite - vocals, acoustic guitar, piano<br />\nTony Gilkyson - guitars<br />\nChris Wagner - bass<br />\nDavid Harte - drums, background vocals<br />\nChris Joyner - piano<br />\nChris Frankfort - lap steel<br />\nNikka Costa - background vocals\n|-\n|2000\n|''Shiva''\n| \n# \"Witches' Hill\" (4:29)\n# \"Ground Zero\" (4:06)\n# \"Back Home\" (4:58)\n# \"I Stopped Asking\" (3:29)\n# \"Safari Song\" (4:06)\n# \"It Ain't My Fault\" (3:46)\n# \"On My Couch\" (4:02)\n# \"You Move Me\" (4:20)\n# \"Stone Cold Alone\" (3:23)\n# \"Bad Old Days\" (3:49)\n# \"Long Lost Man\" (3:48)\n|\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.kathleenwilhoite.com}}\n* {{IMDb name|0001849}}\n* {{tcmdb name|id=206228|name=Kathleen Wilhoite}}\n* [http://love-and-pop.com/kathleen-wilhoite-the-murphys-law-interview/ Interview with Kathleen Wilhoite] 13/12/2013\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wilhoite, Kathleen}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:American female singers]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:American pop singers]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Santa Barbara, California]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Santa Barbara, California]]\n[[Category:Singers from California]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image =\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1964|6|29}}\n| birth_place = [[Santa Barbara, California]], U.S.\n| occupation  = Actress\n| spouse      = {{marriage|David Harte|1997}}\n| children    = 2\n| yearsactive = 1983\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Kathleen Wilhoite''' (born June 29, 1964) is an American stage,<ref>{{cite web|work=[[The New York Times]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/02/04/theater/stage-steve-tesich-s-division-street.html|title=STAGE: STEVE TESICH'S 'DIVISION STREET'|authorlink=Frank Rich|first=Frank|last=Rich|date=February 4, 1987}}</ref> film and television [[actress]],<ref name=NYT>{{cite web|work=[[The New York Times]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/movies/person/116796/Kathleen-Wilhoite|title=Kathleen Wilhoite}}</ref> as well as a singer-songwriter. She is known for her roles in the films ''[[Witchboard]]'' (1986),<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/03/15/movies/love-triangle-in-witchboard.html|title=LOVE TRIANGLE IN 'WITCHBOARD'|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|author=James, Caryn|date=March 15, 1987}}</ref> ''[[Murphy's Law (film)|Murphy's Law]]'' (1986), ''[[Road House (1989 film)|Road House]]'' (1989), ''[[Lorenzo's Oil]]'' (1992), and ''[[The Edge (1997 film)|The Edge]]'' (1997). She is also known for her recurring roles on ''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]'' and ''[[Gilmore Girls]]'', and for voicing the [[title character]] in the animated series ''[[Pepper Ann]]''.\n\n==Career==\nAs a musician, Wilhoite released two albums, ''Pitch Like a Girl'' (1997, Daves' Record Company) and ''Shiva'' (2000, Ruby Ray Records). Her songs have been in such films as ''[[Murphy's Law (film)|Murphy's Law]]'' (1986), which she also starred in;<ref name=ML>{{cite web|work=[[The New York Times]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9A0DE7DD1438F93BA25757C0A960948260|title=Murphy's Law (1986) SCREEN: 'MURPHY'S LAW'|first=Caryn|last=James|date=April 18, 1986}}</ref> her songs have also appeared in ''Valerie Flake'' (1999), and ''East of A'' (2000), ''Touched by an Angel'' (2000), as well as on the television series ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer (TV series)|Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]''. (\"Wish We Never Met\" from ''Pitch Like a Girl'' appeared in the season three episode \"[[Consequences (Buffy episode)|Consequences]]\".)\n\nWilhoite has also starred in films such as ''[[Private School (film)|Private School]]'' (1983),<ref>{{cite news |authorlink=Janet Maslin|last=Maslin |first=Janet |title=Private School (1983) 'PRIVATE SCHOOL' |work=The New York Times |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9900E4D7123BF933A05754C0A965948260 |date=July 30, 1983 |accessdate=January 27, 2012}}</ref> ''[[Angel Heart]] (1987)'', ''[[Road House (1989 film)|Road House]]'' (1989), ''[[Lorenzo's Oil]]'' (1992), ''[[Fire in the Sky]]'' (1993), ''[[Color of Night]]'' (1994), ''[[The Edge (1997 film)|The Edge]]'' (1997), ''[[Drowning Mona]]'' (2000), and ''[[Pay It Forward (film)|Pay It Forward]]'' (2000). She has guest starred in dozens of [[television series]] including ''[[Cop Rock]]'', ''[[The Jeffersons]]'', ''[[Twin Peaks]]'', ''[[Mad About You]]'', ''[[Ally McBeal]]'', ''[[Family Guy]]'', ''[[Quantum Leap (TV series)|Quantum Leap]]'', ''[[Boomtown (2002 TV series)|Boomtown]]'', ''[[Will & Grace]]'', ''[[Charmed]]'', ''[[24 (TV series)|24]]'', ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'', ''[[Criminal Minds]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]'', ''[[The 4400]]'', ''[[The Cleaner (TV series)|The Cleaner]]'', ''[[Boston Legal]]'', ''[[Ghost Whisperer]]'', ''[[Without a Trace]]'' and ''[[The Mentalist]]'', as well as notable recurring roles on ''[[L.A. Law]]'' as Rosalie Hendrickson Stulwicz,<ref name=NYT/> ''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]'' as [[Chloe Lewis (ER)|Chloe Lewis]] and ''[[Gilmore Girls]]'' playing Luke Danes' sister Liz.<ref name=NYT/>\n\nIn May 2006, Wilhoite wrote and performed a [[one-woman show]], ''Stop Yellin''', directed by [[Kathy Najimy]]. The show consisted of autobiographical monologues and performances of songs from her albums.{{citation needed|date=November 2011}}.\n\nWilhoite has also narrated a number of audiobooks, including [[Maria Semple|Maria Semple's]] ''[[Where'd You Go, Bernadette]]'' and ''[[Today Will Be Different]]''.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1983\n|''[[Private School (film)|Private School]]''\n|Betsy\n|\n|-\n|1986\n|''[[Murphy's Law (film)|Murphy's Law]]''\n|Arabella McGee\n|\n|-\n|1986\n|''[[The Morning After (1986 film)|The Morning After]]''\n|Red\n|\n|-\n|1986\n|''[[Witchboard]]''\n|Sarah 'Zarabeth' Crawford\n|\n|-\n|1987\n|''[[Campus Man]]''\n|Molly Gibson\n|\n|-\n|1987\n|''[[Under Cover (1987 film)|Under Cover]]''\n|Corrinne Armour\n|\n|-\n|1988\n|''[[Dream Demon]]''\n|Jenny Hoffman\n|\n|-\n|1988\n|''[[Crossing Delancey]]''\n|Myla Bondy\n|\n|-\n|1989\n|''[[Road House (1989 film)|Road House]]''\n|Carrie Ann\n|\n|-\n|1989\n|''[[Brenda Starr (1989 film)|Brenda Starr]]''\n|Hank O'Hare\n|\n|-\n|1990\n|''[[Everybody Wins (film)|Everybody Wins]]''\n|Amy\n|\n|-\n|1990\n|''[[Bad Influence (film)|Bad Influence]]''\n|Leslie\n|\n|-\n|1992\n|''[[Lorenzo's Oil]]''\n|Deirdre Murphy\n|\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[Fire in the Sky]]''\n|Katie Rogers\n|\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Benders]]''\n|Terri\n|\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Getting Even with Dad]]''\n|Kitty\n|\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Color of Night]]''\n|Michelle\n|\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[The Edge (1997 film)|The Edge]]''\n|Ginny\n|\n|-\n|1997\n|''The Maze''\n|Mira\n|\n|-\n|2000\n|''[[Drowning Mona]]''\n|Lucinda\n|\n|-\n|2000\n|''East of A''\n|Spark\n|\n|-\n|2000\n|''[[Nurse Betty]]''\n|Sue Ann Rogers\n|\n|-\n|2000\n|''Angels!''\n|Georgeanne\n|\n|-\n|2000\n|''[[Pay It Forward (film)|Pay It Forward]]''\n|Bonnie\n|\n|-\n|2003\n|''[[Quicksand (2003 film)|Quicksand]]''\n|Beth Ann\n|\n|-\n|2003\n|''Welcome to the Neighborhood''\n|Jennifer\n|\n|-\n|2004\n|''Perfect Opposites''\n|Terri Curtis\n|\n|-\n|2005\n|''[[Firecracker (film)|Firecracker]]''\n|Jessica\n|\n|-\n|2007\n|''[[King of California]]''\n|Kelly\n|\n|-\n|2008\n|''[[Winged Creatures (film)|Winged Creatures]]''\n|Jenn\n|AKA, ''Fragments''\n|-\n|2009\n|''[[Endless Bummer (film)|Endless Bummer]]''\n|Peggy\n|\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[California Solo]]''\n|Catherine\n|\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Crazy Kind of Love]]''\n|Doris\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[A Sort of Homecoming (film)|A Sort of Homecoming]]''\n|Annie Landry\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''The Dog Lover''\n|Mrs. Gold\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''Ride''\n|Amanda\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1983\n|''[[Quarterback Princess]]''\n|Carolyn\n|TV film\n|-\n|1984\n|''[[AfterMASH]]''\n|Sandy\n|\"Yours Truly, Max Klinger\", \"It Had to Be You\"\n|-\n|1984\n|''[[Family Ties]]''\n|Kathy\n|\"Ready or Not\"\n|-\n|1984\n|''[[Flight 90: Disaster on the Potomac]]''\n|Kelly Duncan\n|TV film\n|-\n|1984\n|''Single Bars, Single Women''\n|Dee Dee\n|TV film\n|-\n|1985\n|''[[Not My Kid]]''\n|Penny\n|TV film\n|-\n|1985\n|''[[The Jeffersons]]''\n|Robin\n|\"State of Mind\"\n|-\n|1985\n|''[[Cagney & Lacey]]''\n|Adrien Wickart\n|\"On the Street\"\n|-\n|1986\n|''[[CBS Schoolbreak Special]]''\n|Paulie\n|\"Have You Tried Talking to Patty?\"\n|-\n|1986\n|''[[Fame (1982 TV series)|Fame]]''\n|Roberta\n|\"W.S.O.A.\"\n|-\n|1986\n|''[[Heart of the City (TV series)|Heart of the City]]''\n|Mary / Tiger Lady\n|\"